column5: Fix for directory listing on Python 2. Pygments expects a string.

Fix ResourceWarning: unclosed file in setup.py

Signed-off-by: MickaÃ«l Schoentgen <contact@tiger-222.fr>
Fixed width of welcome message (prompt_toolkit version was partly invisible).
Implement '-' key binding in file explorer mode.

Implement file explorer. Thanks to David Brochart!

Commit modified by Jonathan Slenders.

fix pyvimrc example

no more `input_processor` module
Implemented breakindent option and added soft wrap mark.
Show correct input mode when in 'temporary navigation mode'.
Removed enter key binding, which is now in prompt_toolkit itself.
Don't include default prompt_toolkit input processors in BufferControl.

Added support for inserting before/after visual block.

(Display multiple cursors and 'INSERT' in status bar.)

Better Jedi integration for completion of Python files.

- Use jedi.Script instead of Jedi.Interpreter
- Also, don't depend on ptpython code anymore.
input_processor.arg is now a string, not a number.
Added Travis built-status to the README.
Added .travis.yml file for Travis integration + more Python versions for tests.
Rewritten tests to pytest, added tox and Readme testing section.
Take output encoding into account in ShowTrailingWhiteSpaceProcessor.
In example config: map jj to esc.
Added shortcuts for many Vi commands.
Added colorcolumn/cc command + added shortcuts for many Vim commands + preview.
Compatibility with latest prompt toolkit refactorings.
Expand path in FileIO.exists. (Fixes bug in ~ expension in :e command.)
A few changes regarding the latest prompt_toolkit (master).
Use six.moves instead of testing for PY3.
Use the focus_stack from BufferMapping. (Change in prompt_toolkit.)
Make sure that 'pyvim -u ...' works also on Python 2.
Use highlighters for search/selection highlighting. (This is much faster.)
Compatibility with prompt_toolkit: get_vi_state API change.
Handle mouse click events on tabs.
Removed on_abort/exit parameters. (IGNORE doesn't exist anymore, and not required.)
Show the current document in the titlebar.
Use Application.style attribute instead of get_style. (Change for the latest prompt_toolkit.)
Added relativenumber, line wrapping, mouse support and compatbility fixes for prompt-toolkit 0.51.
Prompt-toolkit now sends 'buffer' instead of 'document' as the second argument of Processor.run.
Prompt-toolkit now includes the page navigation bindings. We can remove them over here.
Lexer changes to be compatible with the latest prompt-toolkit.
Cleanup for prompt-toolkit==0.44: Using ShowTrailingWhiteSpaceProcessor from prompt_toolkit.
Renamed enable_system_prompt to enable_system_bindings, because it includes also Control-Z suspension.
Upgrade to the latest prompt_toolkit (master branch).
Correctly end files with a trailing newline.
add docopt to install_requires in setup.py
Override ControlT from prompt-toolkit: don't swap characters before cursor.
Fix: use accepts_force also for bw/bd
Added :bd as keybinding to buffer close
Show 'No \! allowed' when used for commands not supporting it.

Fix python 3/2 compatibility for urllib.

Under python3 the urllib2 package doesn't exist anymore.
Used the six alias for it which mimic the python3 api.
Implemented ControlD and ControlU key bindings, for scrolling half a page.
Implemented ControlE and ControlY key bindings
Auto closes new/empty buffers when they are hidden. This solves the :q issue.
Added accept_force parameter to commands decorator. 'bp'/'bn' now also accept an '\!'.
Fix a bug where a user could leave a buffer with unsaved changes by issuing a :b [arg] or :buffer [arg] editor command

Abstraction of I/O backends. Now it is possible to open .gz files and http:// urls.
(And it's very easy to add custom I/O backends.)
Added ControlW n/v key bindings for splitting windows.
Adding shorthands for split and vsplit

Usable pyvim version.
- Layouts: horizontal/vertical splits + tabs.
- Many commands and key bindings.
- Reading and writing of files.
- Pyflakes integration and Jedi for autocompletion.
- ...
